    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM API cost is driven by token volume—input (prompt) and output (completion)—priced per million tokens per model tier. Agent loops multiply small per-call costs; estimation requires summing expected tokens across turns, tools, and retries."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Providers publish price tables (e.g. $0.15 / 1M input tokens for a small model). Total cost = (prompt_tokens × input_rate) + (completion_tokens × output_rate). Cached input, batch APIs, and regional pricing modify rates."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Unbounded agent loops can exceed human labor cost. Product teams need per-session caps, model routing to cheaper SKUs, and forecasts before launching features."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "PRICE_PER_M = {\n    \"gpt-4o-mini\": {\"input\": 0.15, \"output\": 0.60},\n    \"gpt-4o\": {\"input\": 2.50, \"output\": 10.00},\n}\n\ndef estimate_cost(model: str, prompt_tokens: int, completion_tokens: int) -> float:\n    rates = PRICE_PER_M[model]\n    return (prompt_tokens * rates[\"input\"] + completion_tokens * rates[\"output\"]) / 1_000_000\n\n# Agent session: 12 turns, average 8k prompt (growing), 400 completion each\nsession = sum(\n    estimate_cost(\"gpt-4o-mini\", 8000 + i * 500, 400)\n    for i in range(12)\n)\nprint(f\"estimated session USD: {session:.4f}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use it"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Capacity planning before high-traffic agent launch"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Choosing between large vs small model per sub-task"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Setting per-user daily token quotas"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Published rates change—automate updates from provider pages"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Hidden costs: embeddings, rerankers, vector DB, tool API calls"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Caching discounts require architecture support"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Meter usage from API responses, not estimates, in production billing"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Expose cost-per-trace in observability (LangSmith, OpenTelemetry attrs)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Downshift model tier when confidence or task type allows"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cost = input tokens × input rate + output tokens × output rate"
                  }
